#MaySkinChallenge Day 17: Skincare Journey. Boy do we all know me and skin have had a tough relationship! Even in theory when I was doing everything 'right' I was not yielding the results I wanted. If anything, my skin was worse with constant change-ups of products. Consistency is definitely key for me. Since last year I have spend hours and hours researching skincare, ingredients, the science. I was desperate to improve my skin and in turn, feel better about myself. Today, I feel amazing in my own skin. It will never be perfect but it's happy, healthy and I no longer feel at war with it. I truly believe feeling good about your skin should not be a luxury, it's something that we all can and should experience. Now that I'm finishing my degree and thinking about what I want to do in life, nothing pulls me in more than skin and the idea of helping others feel good about themselves. I know how much it hurts and I don't want anyone to feel like that. Connor and I have been sizing what I'll need to do for the correct qualifications and training. It feels right. Maybe this will be the next step in my journey #skin #skincare #skincareroutine
